 **Requirements:** [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/) (`gh`) must be installed and authenticated.
 
+## PR Review Tasks
+
+`takt --pr <number>`, `takt add --pr <number>`, and pipeline `--pr` fetch the PR body, conversation comments, review summaries, and review thread comments as task context. For GitHub PRs, TAKT also detects Markdown image syntax and HTML `<img src="...">` tags that point to GitHub attachment URLs, downloads those images with authenticated `gh` credentials, replaces the original image markup with `[Image #N]`, and passes the downloaded images as task attachments.
+
+Downloaded PR images are copied into `.takt/tasks/<slug>/attachments/` when the task is saved, and `order.md` lists them in the existing attachment section, for example:
+
+```md
+## 添付画像
+
+- [Image #1]: `attachments/image-1.png`
+```
+
+Supported PR image formats are PNG, JPEG, GIF, and WebP. Each image is limited to 10 MiB. TAKT only downloads HTTPS `github.com` attachment URLs such as `github.com/user-attachments/assets/...` and `github.com/<owner>/<repo>/assets/...`; other external image URLs remain in the text and are not fetched. Downloaded images must pass both `Content-Type` validation and magic-byte validation. Missing authentication, download failures, unsupported content types, type mismatches, invalid `Content-Length`, or oversized images fail the PR task input resolution instead of silently dropping the image. GitLab MR providers currently keep the text unchanged and do not download PR image attachments.
+
 ## Task Management Commands
 
 Batch processing using `.takt/tasks.yaml` with task directories under `.takt/tasks/{slug}/`. Useful for accumulating multiple tasks and executing them together later.
